    "summary": "A security vulnerability has been identified in all supported versions of OpenSSL related to the...",
    "details": "A security vulnerability has been identified in all supported versions\n\nof OpenSSL related to the verification of X.509 certificate chains\nthat include policy constraints.  Attackers may be able to exploit this\nvulnerability by creating a malicious certificate chain that triggers\nexponential use of computational resources, leading to a denial-of-service\n(DoS) attack on affected systems.\n\nPolicy processing is disabled by default but can be enabled by passing\nthe `-policy' argument to the command line utilities or by calling the `X509_VERIFY_PARAM_set1_policies()' function.",
    "severity": [
        {
            "type": "CVSS_V3",
            "score": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H"
        }
    ],
